Date: Wed, 23 Sep 2009 09:10:04 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 055/119] venetdev: fix build error

We currently have an issue where the build-system expects a built-in.o
object under kernel/vbus/devices due to an improper use of kconfig
variables.  Lets fix this.

Signed-off-by: Gregory Haskins <ghaskins@novell.com>
---
 kernel/vbus/devices/Makefile |    5 +++--
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/vbus/devices/Makefile b/kernel/vbus/devices/Makefile
index d129948..5becf7c 100644
--- a/kernel/vbus/devices/Makefile
+++ b/kernel/vbus/devices/Makefile
@@ -1,2 +1,3 @@
-obj-$(CONFIG_VBUS_VENETDEV) += venet/
-
+ifdef CONFIG_VBUS_VENETDEV
+obj-y += venet/
+endif
